&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT LOCALCOIN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Localcoin, we aim to empower our customers to join the crypto economy by helping them buy, sell, and convert digital currencies. In addition to running North America’s largest Bitcoin ATM network, we offer an expanding product line that makes digital currencies far more accessible for crypto-enthusiasts in their communities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe that the cryptocurrency space is one that rewards passion, creativity, innovation and those willing to challenge the status quo. As a member of our rapidly-growing team, you’ll join a talented, dynamic group of team members who will encourage you to learn, grow and thrive in your career every step of the way. So if you’re a self-starter looking to hone your skills in a startup environment that fosters innovation, transparency and team connectivity, we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Reporting directly to the Financial Controller, you will work in close collaboration with the Senior Corporate Accountant and review the work of the Staff Accountant. You will be responsible for full cycle accounting and operational finance deliverables while working in unison with several business departments on a weekly basis. You enjoy problem solving to understand large financial and data sets, executing a wide array of financial deliverables and working in a fast paced environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;This position is remote during the pandemic and will be based out of our head office in Toronto, Ontario.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;YOUR IMPACT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Perform full-cycle accounting duties for a group of companies&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Post daily journal entries supported by account reconciliations and back-ups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Prepare schedules, working papers, supporting documents, and analysis to support financial statements, audits, FP&amp;amp;A, and projects&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Responsible for delivering monthly, quarterly, and annual financial close procedures&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Audit and report on high volume crypto and cash flow using key systems and tools&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Review daily Cash-in-Transit (CIT) reconciliations and other work performed by the Staff Accountant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Ensuring accuracy and completion of the general ledger&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Reviewing and auditing the company’s flow of cash and crypto, and maintaining our global companies’ accounting and finance policies and procedures&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Effectively escalate outstanding cash issues with Finance and CIT Partners&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Process banking, payroll, crypto, and other transactions for review and approval by the Finance team and Executives&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Uphold and update accounting policies and documentation for revenue, cost of sales, inventory, fixed assets, loans, and other matters in line with latest ASPE, US GAAP &amp;amp; IFRS guidelines&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Comply with local, provincial, and federal government reporting, licensing and tax requirements&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
