&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DESCRIPTION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data Engineer is an exciting opportunity for a motivated and passionate individual to join the team at Foundry, a subsidiary of the blockchain industry’s most prolific and active investor, Digital Currency Group. Reporting to the CTO, the Data Engineer will help us with in-depth analysis, modeling s and engineering of DeFi and blockchains’ operational and business data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a rare invitation to join a small, highly professional entrepreneurial group, with the backing of the most established player in the fast-growing crypto space.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is based at Foundry HQ in Rochester, NY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRIMARY RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect robust and scalable data collection infrastructure across a variety of protocols&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, research and analyze Operational and Blockchain data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proposes and implements enhancements that will improve the performance and reliability of these data systems over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensures the accuracy and completeness of data in transfer and load to enterprise repositories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishes and maintains security and integrity of controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participates in the formulation and monitoring of policies, procedures and standards relating to data warehouse management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Works with multi-functional project teams that perform: analyze and document business requirements, perform complex data analysis and mapping, and support end-user acceptance testing to support a variety of business intelligence, reporting, analytical and data visualization needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize data, and interpret trends and identify patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with crypto product managers, business analysts and engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand internal data practices in order to identify gaps and areas of inefficiencies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally in order to coordinate and streamline data collection processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write scripts that automate accounting / data processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface closely with Labs team members to understand Foundry’s staking business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead scripting and scraping projects from Proof-of-Stake protocol web pages in order to prepare data sets for modeling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Business Team to identify key data points to capture and archive&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine data architecture to optimize for retrieval&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve resiliency and redundancy of data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refine tool to identify and document public data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Infrastructure Team to analyze infrastructure operational data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retrieve data and logs from various infrastructure systems including provisioning, orchestrating and monitoring systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and manage data lake and data marts for infrastructure data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop data solutions and support infrastructure information gathering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
